<br>
 This is Toll Troll, a long-retired and disaffected warrior of this server.<br>
<br>
Much to my chagrin, I haven't dabbled in the pixelated arcadia of EverQuest in over a year.  With the help of a five-step program and great depths of resolve, I was able to kick it to the curve.  Yet, while I've been indefinitely out of the loop, I've had some time to read up on the next generation of MMORPG's, and must say that the upcoming sequel looks very promising.  <br>
<br>
I have not heard anything of an immediate opening of an &quot;official&quot; role-playing server at release, although I expect there may be a contingent of role-players who flock to a server in specific.  With this apparent successor on the horizon, I was wondering if any of the guilds of the server were planning on re-establishing there? <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.projectbag.com/cowboy_bebop/thumbnails/andy08_t.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:xx-large;"> + </span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.projectbag.com/cowboy_bebop/thumbnails/andy02_t.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:xx-large;"> = </span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://ic.pricegrabber.com/muze_images/Video/Covers/54/102754_89x160.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=valquisssilverpalm>Valquiss Silverpalm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 808<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/4/03 12:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5001.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Any guilds moseyin' to EQ2?</span><hr size=1> I've been waiting for this discussion, and it hasn't begun in earnest yet, but I expect that it will.<br>
<br>
It's my hope, regardless of any designated servers, that the respect-oriented, role-playing contingent of FV will generally agree on an EQ2 server to call their own.  No, we won't be alone there, but at least if we migrate in numbers we can have some effect on the tone of the chosen server.<br>
<br>
For the longest time, for those who can recall back that far, Fenin Ro was the unofficial role-playing server of EQ.  And yes, it was noticable.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
You'll note I used two terms to describe the crowd I appreciate in FV.  But the &quot;role-playing&quot; crowd, and the &quot;respect-oriented&quot; players.  The one does not equal the other, but I think they are mutually complimentary, and I think that both exist in higher proportion on our server.<br>
<br>
Will specific guilds stay largely intact?  Hard to say.  And people who enjoy a variety of experience (good/evil) might find themselves switching &quot;sides.&quot;  Heh.  On that note, I know more players than you might suspect who have taken spins through both the notably &quot;evil&quot; guilds of our server <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>and</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> the notably &quot;good&quot; guilds.  With different characters, naturally.  Some even have alts in both, but it wouldn't be for me to blow the whistle on the ones I know about.  I suspect there are probably more I don't know about also.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Anyway, yeah.  Regardless of whether or not the guilds stay intact, I'd like the core of the server population to stay intact.  Maybe, once server names are announced, this can be determined by a poll or something?  Might also be a good idea to make sure it isn't the same server, as much as possible, as has been designated by some other large group (such as all the PvP people, or Stormhammer, or whatever).  I'd trust the admins on this board to conduct such a survey, and encourage all those I enjoy playing with to go there.<br>
<br>
In any case, I'll go where Saga goes.  Which I hope is the same place the Fellowship goes, which I hope is the same place most of FV goes.<br>
<br>
Valquiss<br>
Retired Enchanter<br>
<br>
